**Problem Description:**

Write a C++ program that takes the following inputs:

1.  The name of a text file.
2.  The word to search for.

The program should read the text file, line by line, and count the number of times the specified word appears in the file. The program should ignore case sensitivity (i.e., "The", "the", and "THE" should all be counted as the same word).

**Input:**

*   The first line of the input will be the name of the text file.
*   The second line will be the word to search for.

**Output:**

*   The program should print the number of occurrences of the word in the file.

**Example:**

**Input:**

```
my_text_file.txt
hello
```

**my_text_file.txt:**

```
Hello world!
This is a test.
hello again.
Hello there!
```

**Output:**

```
3
```

**Skeleton Code:**

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

int main() {
    string filename;
    string wordToSearch;

    // Read filename and word to search from input
    cin >> filename >> wordToSearch;

    // Open the file
    ifstream file(filename);

    // Check if the file opened successfully
    if (!file.is_open()) {
        cerr << "Error opening file: " << filename << endl;
        return 1;
    }

    int count = 0;
    string line;

    // Read the file line by line
    while (getline(file, line)) {
        // Convert the line to lowercase
        transform(line.begin(), line.end(), line.begin(), ::tolower);

        // Convert the word to search to lowercase
        string lowerWord = wordToSearch;
        transform(lowerWord.begin(), lowerWord.end(), lowerWord.begin(), ::tolower);

        // Count the occurrences of the word in the line
        size_t pos = line.find(lowerWord);
        while (pos != string::npos) {
            count++;
            pos = line.find(lowerWord, pos + 1);
        }
    }

    // Close the file
    file.close();

    // Print the count
    cout << count << endl;

    return 0;
}
```

